HEADWORD: Ayle
<hw>Ayle</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>ayel</ets>,
<ets>aiel</ets>, OF. <ets>aiol</ets>, <ets>aiel</ets>, F.
<ets>a⟦ium⟧eul</ets>, a dim. of L. <ets>avus</ets> grandfather.]</ety>
<def>A grandfather.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Writ of Ayle</b></col>, <cd>an ancient English writ which
lay against a stranger who had dispossessed the demandant of land of
which his grandfather died seized.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ayme</ent>⟦br⟧
